DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,3,1);
$d = random(2,7,1);
$b = $a+$d;
$c = random(2,6,1);

$p = random(2,5,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Use Part 2 of the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus to decide if the definite 
integral exists and either evaluate the integral or enter DNE if it does not exist.
$BR
$PAR
   \[ \int_{$a}^{$b} {\frac{$c}{x^$p}} dx \]

   \{ans_rule(35) \} 
$BR
EOT

$Fa = $c*$a**(-$p+1)/(-$p+1);
$Fb = $c*$b**(-$p+1)/(-$p+1);

$ans = "$Fb-($Fa)";
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();
